message.text: There’s nothing like catching up with my neighbors on the street — hearing what’s on their minds, what’s in their hearts. The best policy ideas don’t start in boardrooms — they start on the block. #WoodhavenQueens

message.text: It was a beautiful day at the annual Woodhaven Street Fair with #TeamJenifer! I had a blast greeting hundreds of my neighbors. It’s a staple event every single year, celebrating our community and small businesses. Congratulations to Woodhaven Business Improvement District on another successful festival!

message.text: Last night, I was proud to headline an event to support the Democratic Party’s slate in North Hempstead and Nassau County. Every day, I am grateful to be born in the greatest country on earth. This is election is a fight for the heart and soul of America. Let’s organize and WIN.

message.text:
Today by the Statue of Liberty, I joined @GovKathyHochul and my colleagues to demand an end to Donald Trump’s reckless government shutdown. It’s irresponsible, harmful to working families, and puts New Yorkers’ livelihoods at risk. We need a government that works for the people. 

A shutdown means:
❌ Federal workers furloughed or forced to work without pay
❌ Delays for small business loans & housing programs
❌ Families waiting for food assistance & vital services
This is not leadership.

New Yorkers deserve a government that works for them, not one held hostage by chaos. It’s time to put people over politics, end the shutdown, and get back to serving the American people. 🇺🇸

liveAudioRoomV2StoryMessage.text:
Today by the Statue of Liberty, I joined @GovKathyHochul and my colleagues to demand an end to Donald Trump’s reckless government shutdown. It’s irresponsible, harmful to working families, and puts New Yorkers’ livelihoods at risk. We need a government that works for the people. 

A shutdown means:
❌ Federal workers furloughed or forced to work without pay
❌ Delays for small business loans & housing programs
❌ Families waiting for food assistance & vital services
This is not leadership.

New Yorkers deserve a government that works for them, not one held hostage by chaos. It’s time to put people over politics, end the shutdown, and get back to serving the American people. 🇺🇸
